<span class="displaytext">santa fe, nm -- today, (PARTY NAME) presidential candidate (candidate full) announced the formation of his south carolina steering committee. the committee includes elected officials, (PARTY NAME) activists, members of the business and professional community, and community leaders from around the state. the committee will act as a base of support for (candidate last)'s campaign throughout the state of south carolina. <p>"i am honored to have the support of so many esteemed members of the south carolina community," said governor (candidate last). "they have been leaders in this state, and i know that with their support, we can achieve real change." </p><p>governor (candidate last)'s south carolina campaign will be co-chaired by state representative fletcher smith and former south carolina comptroller general jim lander. </p><p>"i am honored to be a co-chair for governor (candidate last)," said representative fletcher smith. "with his unparalleled record of achievement both in new mexico, creating jobs, expanding the economy and cutting taxes; and on the national and international levels, reopening negotiations in north korea, rescuing american hostages and receiving four nobel peace prize nominations, i know he will make a great president. governor (candidate last) is a true leader who works hard for americans and represents south carolina values and will continue to do that as president." </p><p>"governor (candidate last) has spent the last several decades honing his skills as a leader. i support governor (candidate last) because i know that his vast experience far outshines other candidates and that he will use it effectively for the good of the united states and the world," said former comptroller general jim lander. </p><p><b>(candidate last)</b><b> for president south carolina steering committee:</b> </p><ul><li>fletcher smith, state representative, greenville, <i>co-chair</i></li><li>jim lander, former sc comptroller general, newberry,